    {
      "_id": "H54l2JX2PwNwB7XK",
      "name": "Duplication",
      "type": "pouvoir",
      "img": "https://assets.forge-vtt.com/bazaar/systems/mutants-and-masterminds-3e/assets/assets/icons/pouvoir.svg",
      "system": {
        "type": "attaque",
        "activate": true,
        "special": "standard",
        "action": "simple",
        "portee": "contact",
        "duree": "instantane",
        "notes": "<ul><li><strong>Base Cost:</strong> 1 point per rank</li><li><strong>Heroic Extra:</strong> +2 points per rank (Total 3 points/rank)</li><li><strong>Effect:</strong> Create a duplicate of yourself.</li><li>Duplicate is a minion with the same traits as you, except for this power and any hero points. </li><li>You can spend your own hero points for your duplicate’s actions. </li><li>You must have this power at a rank equal to your own power point total (not counting Duplication), divided by 15, and rounded up for your duplicate to possess your full abilities. </li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">If you have it at a lower rank, create your duplicate as a scaled-down version of yourself, with a power level equal to your rank in this power and starting power points determined accordingly (power rank x 15). </li><li class=\"ql-indent-2\"><em>So a power level 11 hero who has Duplication 8 creates a power level 8 “duplicate” with (8 x 15) 120 power points and proportionately lower-ranked traits. </em></li><li>Your duplicate thinks and acts just like you, so it is automatically helpful toward you. Gamemasters should generally allow the hero’s player to determine the duplicate’s actions. </li><li>Your duplicate disappears if your power is countered for any reason. You can also make your duplicate disappear at will by turning off your power. </li></ul>",
        "effets": "<p>You can create a duplicate of yourself. Your duplicate is a minion with the same traits as you, except for this power and any hero points. You can spend your own hero points for your duplicate’s actions. </p><p><br></p><p><strong>Heroic Extra (Applied):</strong> Removes the \"One-Hit Wonder\" minion rule. The duplicate has a full health track and can take multiple bruises or injuries like a player character.</p>",
        "effetsprincipaux": "Duplicate X% of Self",
        "link": "",
        "descripteurs": {},
        "extras": {
          "klrlbm4lmdl": {
            "name": "Heroic  (Summoning)",
            "type": "extra",
            "description": "<ul><li><strong>No \"One-Hit Wonder\" Rule:</strong>&nbsp;Standard minions are incapacitated the moment they fail a single resistance check, regardless of the degree of failure. A Heroic duplicate has a full health track and can take multiple bruises or injuries just like you.</li><li><strong>Action Economy:</strong>&nbsp;Heroic duplicates do not have the&nbsp;<strong>Dazed</strong>&nbsp;condition when summoned. This means they get a full set of actions (Standard, Move, and Free) every round without you needing to apply the \"Active\" modifier separately, as Heroic already includes it.</li><li><strong>Critical Hits:</strong>&nbsp;Minions cannot score critical hits against non-minions, but&nbsp;<strong>Heroic</strong>&nbsp;duplicates can, making them much more dangerous in a fight.</li><li><strong>No Routine Attacks:</strong>&nbsp;Enemies can normally take a \"routine check\" (treating their d20 roll as a 10) to automatically hit a minion. They cannot do this against a Heroic duplicate; they must roll to hit.</li></ul>",
            "rang": 1,
            "edit": true,
            "cout": {
              "fixe": false,
              "rang": true,
              "value": 2
            },
            "details": true,
            "data": {
              "cout": {
                "value": null
              }
            }
          },
